  "text": "The Kafka Connect plugin/extension loading system lives entirely in the `connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/` package. The core components are: (1) **PluginClassLoader** - a child-first URLClassLoader that loads plugin classes in isolation, using `PluginUtils.shouldLoadInIsolation` to decide delegation; (2) **DelegatingClassLoader** - the top-level classloader that routes class loading to per-plugin PluginClassLoaders, maintains a registry of plugin descriptors to classloaders, and supports versioned plugin loading; (3) **PluginScanner** (abstract) with two implementations: **ReflectionScanner** (uses ClassGraph to scan classpaths reflectively for subclasses of plugin interfaces) and **ServiceLoaderScanner** (uses java.util.ServiceLoader); (4) **Plugins** - the main orchestrator that initializes scanning via `initLoaders`, creates plugin instances via `newConnector`/`newConverter`/`newHeaderConverter`/`newPlugin` (interface-based dependency injection using reflection instantiation and `Configurable.configure()`), and manages classloader context switching via `compareAndSwapLoaders`. Supporting types include PluginDesc (descriptor), PluginScanResult (aggregated scan output), PluginSource (record of a plugin location + loader), PluginType (enum mapping plugin interfaces), PluginUtils (path scanning, isolation rules, alias computation), ClassLoaderFactory/PluginClassLoaderFactory (factory interfaces), LoaderSwap (AutoCloseable for classloader swapping), PluginDiscoveryMode (enum for scan strategy selection), and VersionedPluginLoadingException. The plugin interfaces themselves (Connector, Converter, HeaderConverter) are defined in the connect-api module.",
